.SS Command Palette
Press
.B :
in any view (except settings) to open the command palette.
Type commands with arguments. An autocomplete dropdown appears above the input.
.TS
l l.
Command	Description
_
:delete	Delete selected item
:pin	Toggle pin on session
:resume	Resume session
:fork	Fork session
:view	View item detail
:copy	Copy session ID
:new [path]	New session
:new skill [name]	Create new skill
:rename <name>	Rename session
:edit	Edit in $EDITOR
:export <html|md>	Export session
:filter <query>	Filter current list
:sort <field>	Sort sessions (date/name/directory)
:set <key> <value>	Change a setting
:theme <name>	Switch theme
:settings	Open settings
:tab <name>	Switch tab
:quit	Quit
:help [command]	Show help
.TE
.PP
Commands are context-aware (only relevant commands appear).
History persists across sessions in
.IR ~/.config/tracer/history .
.SS Settings View
.TS
l l.
Key	Action
_
\(ua/\(da	Navigate settings
\(<-/\(->	Change value
Enter	Change value
Esc	Save and go back
.TE
.SH SETTINGS
Accessible via the
.B s
key from the list view, the
.B tracer settings
command, or by editing
.IR ~/.config/tracer/config.json .
.TP
.B Theme
Color theme. Run \fBtracer theme\fR to preview all available themes.
.TP
.B Sort by
Default sort order: date (newest first), name (alphabetical), or directory.
.TP
.B Show date
Toggle the Date column in the list view.
.TP
.B Show directory
Toggle the Directory column in the list view.
.TP
.B Show branch
Toggle the Branch column in the list view.
.TP
.B Confirm delete
When on, deleting a session requires a y/N confirmation.
When off, sessions are deleted immediately.
.TP
.B Auto update
When on, checks for updates in the background and installs after the TUI exits.
Off by default.
.TP
.B Cmd dropdown
Show autocomplete dropdown in the command palette. On by default.
.TP
.B Ghost suggest
Show inline ghost text suggestion in the command palette. Off by default.
.TP
.B Max suggestions
Maximum number of suggestions shown in the command palette dropdown (3\-12). Default 8.
.SH DETAIL VIEW
The detail view shows session metadata including:
.IP \(bu 2
Session ID, date, working directory, git branch
.IP \(bu 2
Message count (user and assistant)
.IP \(bu 2
Context usage progress bar (tokens used vs. model context window)
.IP \(bu 2
Output token count
.IP \(bu 2
Scrollable conversation preview
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.claude/projects/{path}/{sessionId}.jsonl
Session conversation files. Each JSONL line is a message entry.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/history.jsonl
Global history log. Used to detect /rename commands.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/file\-history/{sessionId}/
File version history per session. Deleted when a session is removed.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/tasks/{sessionId}/
Task definitions per session. Deleted when a session is removed.
.TP
.I ~/.config/tracer/config.json
Persistent settings (theme, sort order, column visibility, confirm delete, auto update).
.TP
.I ~/.config/tracer/pins.json
Pinned session IDs.
.TP
.I ~/.config/tracer/renames.json
Custom session names set from within tracer.
.TP
.I ~/.config/tracer/history
Command palette history. One command per line, max 100 entries.
.TP
.I ~/.config/tracer/exports/
Exported session Markdown files. Created by pressing \fBx\fR in the detail view.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/settings.json
Global Claude Code permission settings (allow/deny rules). Managed via the Permissions tab.
.TP
.I {project}/.claude/settings.json
Project-level permission settings. Shared with collaborators.
.TP
.I {project}/.claude/settings.local.json
Local project permission settings. Not committed to git.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate the
.I ~/.claude/
directory and to shorten paths in the display.
.TP
.B EDITOR
Used by the
.B e
key in the detail view to open the session file for editing.
Falls back to
.B vi
if not set.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit.
.TP
.B 1
Error (failed to scan sessions, update failure, etc.)
.SH EXAMPLES
Launch the TUI:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer
.RE
.PP
Check current version:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer \-\-version
.RE
.PP
Update to the latest release:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer update
.RE
.PP
Open interactive theme picker:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer theme
.RE
.PP
Set theme directly:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer theme dracula
.RE
.PP
Open settings:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer settings
.RE
